   TORRANCE, Calif. -- International Technology Corp. said it
received a seven-year contract with an estimated value of
$41.7 million from New York City's Department of Sanitation.
   The company said the contract involves design and
implementation of a system that would collect and treat
potentially hazardous substances to prevent groundwater and
air contamination.
